Description: Denotes the diameter of the circular opening of the net used for zooplankton sampling. This measurement is typically expressed in centimeters (cm) and is a used to calculate the volume of water filtered during sampling and the efficiency of zooplankton collection. A larger net diameter allows for a greater volume of water to pass through, increasing the likelihood of capturing a diverse and representative sample of zooplankton from the aquatic environment.

Specifies the size of the openings in the mesh material used for zooplankton (or similar) sampling nets. This measurement is typically recorded in micrometers (m) and is a critical parameter that determines the types and sizes of zooplankton that can be effectively captured and studied. Smaller mesh sizes will capture smaller zooplankton, while larger mesh sizes are suitable for capturing larger specimens.
